# step

`wt step <action>` is @wt/merge and @wt/switch decomposed into reusable phases.
Use a step when you want just one stage — commit now, rebase now — rather than the
whole land-it pipeline. Several actions reuse the LLM commit generator configured
in @wt/config (`[commit.generation]`).

| Recipe | Action | Does |
|--------|--------|------|
| `commit` | `commit` | stage + commit with an LLM-generated message |
| `squash` | `squash [target]` | fold the branch's commits into one (LLM message) |
| `rebase` | `rebase` | rebase the current branch onto its target |
| `push` | `push` | fast-forward the target branch to this branch |
| `diff` | `diff [target]` | everything since branching: committed+staged+unstaged+untracked |
| `copy-ignored` | `copy-ignored` | copy gitignored files into another worktree |

`copy-ignored` is the build-cache sharer — it carries `.env`, `node_modules`,
`target/` and friends into a fresh worktree so it builds without a cold start.
`diff` is broader than `git diff`: it spans the whole divergence including
untracked files. Experimental actions also exist (`eval`, `for-each`, `promote`,
`prune`, `relocate`, `tether`) — check `wt step --help`.

```just
# stage + commit with an LLM-generated message
commit:
  wt step commit

# fold the branch's commits into one (LLM message)
squash target="":
  wt step squash {{target}}

# rebase the current branch onto its target
rebase:
  wt step rebase

# fast-forward the target branch to this branch
push:
  wt step push

# everything changed since branching (committed+staged+unstaged+untracked)
diff target="":
  wt step diff {{target}}

# copy gitignored files (build cache, .env) into another worktree
copy-ignored:
  wt step copy-ignored
```
